- 'young drivers' refers to drivers born in the 1990s;
- 'top four' refers to finishing positions less than 5.

- "Speed demons" refers to drivers with the highest average speeds;
- The ranking is based on average speed, not the fastest single lap or race;
- Each track has its own set of top 3 drivers, independent of other tracks.

- "lightning-fast driver" refers to the driver with the highest average speed on a track;
